### 3.4 Potential Implications and Limitations
FRM offers a synthesis of fractal and adaptive dynamics, potentially convenient as an integrated exploratory tool combining existing methods for examining regime shifts in non-stationary systems. It incorporates dissipation thresholds and adaptive couplings, though it does not demonstrate superior predictive performance over existing MF-DFA + Kuramoto hybrids. Limitations include reliance on established methods and modest empirical novelty. Future work could explore quantitative out-of-sample comparisons and broader datasets.

## 4. Empirical Illustrations (Expanded)
### 4.1 BTC Time Series (Finance Illustration)
Data: Daily log-returns from Yahoo Finance/Bitstamp (2019–2023 actual; 2024–2026 projected via ARIMA [Tang, 2025]; note: ARIMA assumes linearity and may deviate in high volatility). MF-DFA (q = -5 to +5) yields generalized Hurst h(q) ~0.6–0.7 (bubbles), Δα ~0.4–0.6 ± 0.05 (bootstrap), post-2022 entropy gains ~0.1–0.3 bits. Values derived from Fracttalix MF-DFA (daily frequency) and are consistent with multifractal trends in [Bucur et al., 2025; Tang, 2025] (Tang reports Hurst ≈0.58 → 0.465 at 10-min frequency, reflecting timescale differences). Surrogate (AAFT, 1000 replicates): p < 0.01 rejecting monofractal null.

**Table 1: Comparison of Sentinel vs. Fixed-Threshold Baseline (Synthetic Persistent Drift, N=1000)**  
| Method               | False Positives (%) | Detection Latency (points) | Regime Reset Success (%) |
|----------------------|---------------------|----------------------------|--------------------------|
| Sentinel (adaptive)  | 1.7                 | 9–14                       | 98                       |
| Fixed Threshold (3σ) | 4.2                 | 18–25                      | 82                       |

Note: This comparison is on synthetic persistent drift data (N=1000); real-world performance may vary.

### 4.2 HRV in Physiological Rhythms
Data: PhysioNet nsrdb/MIT-BIH (healthy subsets). DFA yields α1 ~0.85 ± 0.08 (healthy awake), dropping to ~0.65 under stress [Tan, 2009; Tulppo et al., 2005; Gronwald et al., 2020; Billman, 2011]. Surrogates: σ_sur ~0.04.

